# AI-Assisted Work - Cursor Rules

This folder contains Cursor rules for AI-assisted work management.

## Available Rules

### Work Management

| Rule | Command | Purpose |
|------|---------|---------|
| `start-work.mdc` | `/start-work` | Initialize new work items |
| `progress-work.mdc` | `/progress-work` | Continue work on items |
| `work-status.mdc` | `/work-status` | Report work item status |
| `pivot-work.mdc` | `/pivot-work` | Rescope and replan |
| `complete-work.mdc` | `/complete-work` | Finalize work items |

### ASCII Image

| Rule | Command | Purpose |
|------|---------|---------|
| `replace-ascii-diagrams.mdc` | `/replace-ascii` | Convert ASCII to images |

## Installation

Copy these files to your project's `.cursor/rules/` folder:

```bash
cp -r ai-assisted-work/agents/cursor-rules/*.mdc your-project/.cursor/rules/
```

## Usage

In Cursor, type the command (e.g., `/start-work`) to activate the agent.
